description:
What would happen if the sea would never move again? many would call it calm, but all are points of view, if calm would take over a force in constant chaos, chaos would surround the rest of things, what would happen in the mind of a fish that simply swam around? surely chaos, its world stopped, it cannot move, it cannot oxygenate, it cannot do anything but agonize slowly where once seconds ago it was happy or simply lived…
Simple analogy, but how relevant is a fish? or all fish? what about the rest of the living beings? the water would become a kind of completely solid liquid, without movement, slow, but how bad would it be?
